Shield gun, Primary; charges a melee attack that deals 150 damage. If you manage to get to him. ;) Secondary; A shield that slowly degenerates over time. It doesn't protect your legs.Useless against rockets, mini-gun, flak and shock combo's. Close range, not advised. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/61\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/61\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet1.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

S.M.G., Primary, very weak and inaccurate automatic fire. Do not use this. Secondary, Grenades deal a steady 70 damage. Charge them full and use them as ghetto rockets. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/1\/19\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet2.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Bio-rifle, primary; Little green blobs doing 40 damage when they hit. On the ground they act like mines exploding after 5 seconds. Secondary, Charge up a big blob doing a whopping 250 damage in the case of a direct hit. Hard to aim. Medium close range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/81\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/8\/81\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet3.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Shock-rifle, arguably the most useful weapon. Primary; a hit-scan doing 40 damage. Secondary; a slow moving bolt doing 45 damage. Combo; Shoot the secondary with the primary shot and BOOM. Long to medium range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/4\/40\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/4\/40\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet4.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Mini-gun, Primary, powerful machine gun, inaccurate. Secondary, extremely accurate machine gun, at expense of damage. Close to medium range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet5.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/6\/63\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet5.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Link-gun, Highest DPS weapon, although easily dodged. Primary shoots green bolts. Extremely useful in close combat. Secondary is a constant stream doing 50 damage per sec. Close range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet6.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/c\/cd\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet6.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Rocket launcher. Primary shoots a single rocket, medium range. Secondary charges a 2 to 3 rocket barrage. By keeping the right button pressed and clicking left, you can shoot a 3 rocket spiral. Medium close range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/7f\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet7.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/7\/7f\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet7.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

Flak cannon, Primary, shoots out hot chunks of metal, in a shotgun like fashion. Useful in close combat. Secondary is a grenade/mortar, direct hit does 90-160 damage. Close to medium range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0a\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet8.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/0\/0a\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet8.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

LG, A sniper with a beacon so everyone knows where you are. Direct hit deals 70 damage, head shot makes for 140. Secondary is the zoom. Long medium range. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/d\/dc\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet9.jpg\/v4-460px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","bigUrl":"\/images\/thumb\/d\/dc\/Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet9.jpg\/aid200771-v4-728px-Do-Well-in-Unreal-Tournament-2004-Step-3Bullet9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fair_use\">Fair Use<\/a> (screenshot)<br>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

